SIMPLE: fusil
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fusil
<hw>Fu"sil</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>fusilis</ets>
molten, fluid, fr. <ets>fundere</ets>, <ets>fusum</ets>, to pour, cast.
See <er>Fuse</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Capable of
being melted or rendered fluid by heat; fusible.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧A kind of <xex>fusil</xex> marble⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Woodward.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Running or flowing, as a liquid.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>fusil</xex> sea.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>J.
Philips.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Formed by melting and pouring into a mold; cast;
founded.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fusil</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fusil
<hw>Fu"sil</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>fusil</ets>,
LL. <ets>fosile</ets> a steel for kindling fire, from L.
<ets>focus</ets> hearth, fireplace, in LL. fire. See <er>Focus</er>, and
cf. <er>Fusee</er> a firelock.]</ety> <def>A light kind of flintlock
musket, formerly in use.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fusil</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Fusil
<hw>Fu"sil</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See 3d <er>Fusee</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>A bearing of a rhomboidal figure; -- named from
its shape, which resembles that of a spindle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It differs from a lozenge in being longer in proportion
to its width.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fusile</ent>⟦br⟧
